node.text: If you read my book "Heels of Steel" you know it was based on my real life experiences, in the #NYC, male dominated world of construction. Well this guy thought he was my BOSS, and tried to undermine me by asking if I knew how to read this set of blueprints, in front of my client - so what happened next? I fired him! 🛠 What would you have done? 👇🏻#msbarbarak

node.text:
I'm off from work day! 
The first Labor Day was celebrated in 1882 in NYC and became an official holiday in 1894. Women took hold of the Labor Department from the start and it was the first agency led by a woman, Frances Perkins, with six women holding the title since. Our city and its people are so unique! 
Hope everyone is enjoying their day off! #LaborDay

node.text: It was a weekend of balls and hurricanes! Such an amazing cause and event at this years #AngelBall2021 and Hurricane Henri certainly didn’t stop us from anything!🤣 What did you guys do this weekend? #msbarbarak
